The paper deals with enhancing privacy protections of databases, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of game theory to model the interaction between the auditor and potential attackers suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The proposed approach involves linear programming, column generation, and heuristic search, which are common techniques in the data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with auditing policies for databases, which suggests that it may also belong to the databases (cs.DB) sub-category.
